  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package contains a subtle W-AR-05 weakener: the primary validation result omits a comparedAgainst link, and the secondary result references a comparator dataset collected under ventricular assist device (VAD) operating pressures rather than CPB circuit pressures, making it structurally present but inferentially mismatched for the declared COU.",
