      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry using meshes of 1.2M, 4.8M, and 19.2M cells. Richardson extrapolation yielded a GCI of 3.1% for volume-averaged shear stress and 2.8% for NHI at the 2500 RPM, 4.0 L/min operating point, representative of the worst-case hemolysis condition. GCI < 5% criterion satisfied."
    },
    {
