      "rationale": "The primary PIV dataset (Morrison et al. 2019) was collected using a blood-analogue glycerol–water mixture (μ = 3.5 mPa·s, ρ = 1050 kg/m³) at CPB-representative flow rates (2.5–6.0 L/min) and rotational speeds (2000–3500 RPM). Inlet and outlet pressures were documented. Test conditions are considered representative of CPB operating range. The secondary hemolysis bench dataset was collected at VAD pressures; this distinction is noted in the secondary validation result."
