      "rationale": "NHI and RH are standard hemolysis metrics used in FDA guidance for blood-contacting device evaluation. RH < 1 relative to predicate is the acceptance criterion stated in the COU. These QoIs directly support the decision to identify worst-case operating conditions and are appropriate for MRL 2."
