      "rationale": "Validation was conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry, which is the same geometry used in the COU simulations. Blood-analogue fluid properties matched CPB-representative values. Operating points span the full COU flow-speed matrix. The validation team concluded that the validation activities are sufficiently relevant to the COU at MRL 2, noting that the secondary hemolysis comparator dataset introduces a pressure-regime difference that is addressed by the Giersiepen–Wurzinger model's pressure-independence assumption."
