    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors were not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 scoping for a Class II device with Medium model influence. The primary validation result demonstrates RH < 1.0 across all five CPB operating points with mean NHI prediction error within ±12%. The secondary validation result provides supporting evidence of hemolysis damage model fidelity using the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry under overlapping flow conditions. The assessment team concluded that the CFD model provides adequate credibility for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions under CPB use, and the decision to accept the model predictions for tolerance analysis is supported.",
